    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:1",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "HPI: 50M with a fib noncompliant on coumadin, CAD s/p stent x6, CHF    with dias",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s1",
      "text": "HPI: 50M with a fib noncompliant on coumadin, CAD s/p stent x6, CHF    with diastolic dysfunction, HTN, morbid obesity, alcoholism, and DM tx    from [**Hospital6 3044**] for poss intervention following CVA."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:2",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Patient presented on [**11-19**] with 2d of general malaise, abd pain, one    bo",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s2",
      "text": "Patient presented on [**11-19**] with 2d of general malaise, abd pain, one    bout of emesis, near syncope during micturition as well as tinnitus."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:3",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "He    was noted to be hypotensive upon arrival to the ED, which resolved    foll",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s3",
      "text": "He    was noted to be hypotensive upon arrival to the ED, which resolved    following fluid boluses."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:4",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Head CT showed likely old parietal infarct and    possible area of low attenuati",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s4",
      "text": "Head CT showed likely old parietal infarct and    possible area of low attenuation in the central pons (?infarct)."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:5",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "CT    abd/chest no evidence of aortic dissection.",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s5",
      "text": "CT    abd/chest no evidence of aortic dissection."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:6",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "On presentation his INR was    1.0, PT 10.5s and PTT 26.1s. 11:35am [**11-19**] ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s6",
      "text": "On presentation his INR was    1.0, PT 10.5s and PTT 26.1s. 11:35am [**11-19**] transient slurring of    speech, with normal upper and lower extremity strength, tone,    and sensation bilaterally. 18:00 his speech was still slurred with    decreased LUE and LLE strength ([**5-29**] -> [**4-29**])."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:7",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "At 20:00 he began to have    an expressive language difficulty along with his sl",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s7",
      "text": "At 20:00 he began to have    an expressive language difficulty along with his slurred speech, with    right facial drooping, he also had a poor cough and difficulty clearing    his secretions."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:8",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "MRI/MRA head/neck [**11-19**] showed possible basilar artery    thrombosis with ",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s8",
      "text": "MRI/MRA head/neck [**11-19**] showed possible basilar artery    thrombosis with multiple infarcts in the brainstem and cerebellar    hemispheres."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:9",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "He was note to have absent gag later in morning and he was    intubated prior to",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s9",
      "text": "He was note to have absent gag later in morning and he was    intubated prior to arrival in ICU for airway protection."
    },
    {
      "id": "E:note:row498276:10",
      "kind": "note_sentence",
      "display": "Fever (Hyperthermia, Pyrexia, not Fever of Unknown Origin)    Assessment:    Tem",
      "code": null,
      "value": null,
      "unit": null,
      "effective": null,
      "source_ref": "note:row498276#s10",
      "text": "Fever (Hyperthermia, Pyrexia, not Fever of Unknown Origin)    Assessment:    Temp 102.5 max    BAL gm+cocci and gm-rods    Action:    No cultures per SICU resident    Tylenol and cooling    Frequent suction    Tube feeds held at MN and heparin gtt stopped @2am    Response:    Temp improved    Plan:    Ongoing, continue ABX and Tylenol    Will still plan PEG today    Respiratory failure, acute (not ARDS/[**Doctor Last Name 11**])    Assessment:    Saturations 92-96% one episode of drop to 88%    Action:    Peep increased to 8 and FIO2 increased to 60%    Response:    copious amts of secretions persist    Plan:    trach collar for short sprints"
    }
  ],
